    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it doesn't feel like anxiety. anxiety is like a racing heart or sweating, but this is different. it's like a precise, rhythmic pulsing that matches the frequency of the intraday trades. i saw it happen with the big dip at 2pm today—i felt the exact same rhythm in my temples five minutes before the sell-off started. it's too specific to just be \"stress.\" doesn't it make sense that there could be some kind of bio-digital feedback loop happening? like, if the algos are driving the market, and we're all connected via these high-frequency waves, maybe some people are just more sensitive to it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
